hmm, I think we were talking about xp groups here, where mana IS important<br>
<br>
I don't think most knights feel we need to grab aggro and tank on raids, and we realize that this is not our job.  There is a tradeoff every time you try to optimize a group.  If you want better aggro control, you need a cleric with very good mana regen and VoQ, or you might need a secondary healer.  That healer has to then stop contributing all mana to group DPS.<br>
<br>
If you want to talk about the kunark era 75/25, lets talk about the kunark era xp penalty.  Ya know how many people I saw as a troll SK level from 28 to 36 while I worked on 35 in old CT as a troll SK? It was ridiculous.  I think it took something like 2 months on my play time.  Anyone remember that?  Would I love the exp penalty back in? yes, it stops a bunch of mindless twinks and class envy. <br>
<br>
However, we are talking about PoP exp groups here.  The game has changed, evolved.  For the better? I think so.  Do you guys need help with aggro in exp groups without EB weapons? (and maybe with?)  I would say so.  However, I, just to test it out, taunted in an exp group using just lifetaps, slam, my taunt/disarm hotkey, and snaring at 15%.  Was it as effective as spamming Clinging Darkness or Terror line? No.  Did it work? Yes.  I won't deny that you guys, even the most intelligent and experienced of you, need help, but I won't stand by while you call nerf on my class because you are either ignorant or jealous.<br>
