As far as I can tell most warriors want one of a few things. Much more hp than a knight can get, better taunt, or better innate mitigation. SOMETHING that would give warriors an innate advantage over knights to make up for knights innate ability to lock agro on themselves. Personally, im in favor of an innate damage reduction thats warrior only. After all, they are warriors. They should be tougher than any other fighting class and so, should take less damage per hit than any other. Now THAT would make for a tough choice! Do i take the knight who is a more than capable tank and can hold agro firmly, or do I take the warrior that may have a harder time with agro but takes less damage than a knight?<br>
Oh, and incidently, I agree. DAOC has a FAR superior combat system to eq. Its only downside is a lack of high end content beyond killing a single dragon for each realm and pvp.<br>
