<br>
The long standing argument against making warriors grab aggro effectively has been &quot;It would trivialize the game.&quot;<br>
<br>
But doesn't it &quot;trivialize the game&quot; if Paladins and SK's can pretty much do that anyways? They can get and hold aggro extremely effectively. And yet, the game isn't trivialized by this?<br>
<br>
So why not just do what warriors have been asking for, for ages? Why not just FIX the warriors? Give them something that will get aggro reasonably effectively. Or something that will MANAGE aggro reasonably effectively.<br>
<br>
Sure, taunt's been fixed quite a bit from this time last year. But with the move to the planes of power, that fix to taunt has been negated by and large.<br>
<br>
Would fixing warrior aggro abilities trivialize the game? I mean, really?<br>
<br>
/sigh<br>
