<br>
I agree, it wouldn't.  But it does have the Knights scared spitless that they suddenly will be ostracized as a result. What they fail to take into account is that all three plate melee tank just fine for the majority of group situations.  Even if Warriors had an ability to get earlier aggro, this wouldn't make much difference.  It would mean that people would be willing to pick up much any tank LFG rather than having a definite preference.   And it would make grouping with a Warrior less of a chore for all concerned.<br>
<br>
They feel our HP makes us more attractive, but the difference is small enough and the mobs in PoP hit hard enough, that it really doesn't make that big a difference.  If the mobs where hitting for 100 damage a swing, then 800ish more HP would make a difference.  When they're hitting for 500+, it's kind of moot.  An advantage, sure.  A huge advantage, hardly.<br>
<br>
Once you start including things like heals, life taps, additional offensive dots/nukes, stuns, snares, roots, and such, it's kind of hard to say the Warrior's 50ish more AC and 800ish more HP is so telling that he deserves to suck on initial aggro control to the extremely high degree the majority of Warriors do.<br>
<br>
