<br>
The argument that giving warriors a way to generate initial aggro would trivialize raid encounters is bogus.  It would change very little in the current raiding environment.   Every raid which I've tanked, aggro control has been trivial anyhow, the only exceptions being those where aggro reducer procs are implemented, which still don't do much against taunt aggro, only proc and spell aggro, and it's pretty easy to compensate for those raids.<br>
<br>
It's simply what I like to call 'the truth of the cliche'&quot;  You say something enough times and regardless of how incorrect, people still believe it.<br>
<br>
Other examples of lies passed on as truth via repitition:<br>
<br>
Warriors have a mitigation advantage over Knights<br>
<br>
Beg increases aggro<br>
<br>
Low Charisma helps with fear<br>
<br>
the list can go on and on of myths believed because people repeat them. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=dobbanz>dobbanz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>/cons RED</span><br>  Posts: 398<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/18/03 8:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1882.topic&index=69>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_ale.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: what needs to be fixed</span><hr size=1> Dont forget MY favorite. &quot;Monks will be tanking raid level ubermobs.&quot;<br>
