<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>most warriors are NOT calling for nerfs on anyone<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
And remember when the discussion moved to monks being better &quot;tanks&quot; than the tanks were?  And the results after that?  No, you may not be asking for nerfs, but if VI/sony feels that an encounter is balanced against existing abilities, do you honestly expect them to improve on the tanking abilities of the Warrior, and then rebalance all the conent against the new standard?  or just adjust other classes to give warriors their perceived gains in agro ability?  If it were my decision to make, I would take the path of less resistance and simply lower existing abilities, rather than have to go back and review all current content and see if it's balanced.<br>
<br>
Second thing, you cannot consider xp groups totally seperate raid groups.  Any changes made for the betterment of a class in it's Group abilities, is just magnified in a raid.  Giving warriors fast, assured agro, with the backup of the warrior disciplines would be overpowering vs content.<br>
<br>
And third, so many warriors keep saying &quot;fix&quot; warrior taunt.  Well, what is the fix?  And just how does that &quot;fix&quot; not trivialize content that is balanced against warriors abilities hedged with unsure hate generation? <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://spin.emich.edu/sig/utal3.gif"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--><br>
