<br>
How is this true for warriors and NOT true for knights, who CAN taunt reliably? How is it, with a knight tanking and holding aggro like GLUE, the game is NOT trivialized, but with a warrior, anything short of ping ponging makes the game too easy?<br>
<br>
How is it, with knights making the game easy, everything is fine and hunky dory, but with warriors, it has to be hard?<br>
<br>
It sounds so much like a double standard.<br>
<br>
&quot;but if VI/sony feels that an encounter is balanced against existing abilities, do you honestly expect them to improve on the tanking abilities of the Warrior, and then rebalance all the conent against the new standard?&quot;<br>
<br>
A lot of encounters are currently unbalanced in the planes of power. From casters soloing through trash mobs in low tiers, to melees having practically nothing to do against big mobs in the top planes.<br>
<br>
I think SOE already knows its encounters are unbalanced.<br>
<br>
&quot;rather than have to go back and review all current content and see if it's balanced.&quot;<br>
<br>
They're already having to go back and review current content. Case in point, they rejiggered, Sol Ro, Rallos Zek, Xegony ... I'm sure their Rathe encounter is pretty much FUBAR. I shudder to think what people are going to encounter when they finally do break through the muddled events and the whacky coding and enter the plane of timesink.<br>
<br>
&quot;Giving warriors fast, assured agro, with the backup of the warrior disciplines would be overpowering vs content.&quot;<br>
<br>
How is this different from giving knights, fast, assured aggro?<br>
<br>
/disc defensive? A lot of warriors claim they use evasive almost as much these days.<br>
<br>
And currently having warriors unable to hold aggro reliably enough that they can't even GET groups to get XP is also broken.<br>
<br>
It needs to be fixed. As a knight, I guess you have a hard time seeing that. But seriously, understand for a moment ... casters are lazy, they do not want ping ponging when they finally show enough gumption to group.<br>
<br>
Because of this they by and large do not want warriors in their groups in the trash mob planes. What's worse is, the word is out now. So this is becoming commonplace dreck for your standard pickup group. People are believing the hype and going with knights over warriors, even warriors who can hold aggro reliably.<br>
<br>
/shrug<br>
<br>
It's something that needs to be tweaked, and fixed. Not a huge fix. Not a game changing, content trivializing fix. Just a fix.<br>
<br>
Fix taunt. It shouldn't be so hard should it?<br>
<br>
I'm sure many many warriors in the game would take a reliable taunt over disc defensive and enraging blow weapons. <br>
<br>
&quot;Well, what is the fix?&quot;<br>
<br>
Many suggestions have been made about how to fix taunt on many threads.<br>
<br>
One of them was to make it, for warriors only, a SCALING ability that changed over time.<br>
<br>
Like monk special attacks. As monks level up, their KICK becomes Round Kick, Tiger Claw, Eagle Strike, Dragon Punch and finally Flying Kick.<br>
<br>
Well, make it for warriors, as THEY level up, taunt becomes Aggravate, Instigate, Provoke and JOMAMMA!<br>
<br>
And make it work better as they acquire these new special taunts.<br>
<br>
It's just one of the many suggestions. People have made on the myriad of threads kicking around here.<br>
<br>
&quot;And just how does that &quot;fix&quot; not trivialize content that is balanced against warriors abilities hedged with unsure hate generation? &quot;<br>
<br>
Well two things: 1) Content is already trivialized by Paladins and Shadowknights in regards to aggro and hate generation. It won't really affect much to FIX taunt other than giving warriors the FIX they need to be slightly more effective in groups. In other words, BALANCING warriors so that Warriors, Paladins OR SK's can do the same job in groups. Right now, there are frequent times they can't. The TRIVIAL aggro holding abilities of knights or at least the HYPE about them, is making warriors less desirable.<br>
<br>
2) By fixing taunt, it balances the game a little bit. Why is this such a bad thing to knights? What is it knights fear so damn much about a warrior being able to keep a mob from ping ponging a little more reliably than they currently do?<br>
<br>
-Wubao<br>
Grandmaster of Povar <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=krazrussian>KrazRussian</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 98<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/21/03 1:41 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1882.topic&index=75>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_ale.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: same old lame debate</span><hr size=1> Keep this in mind when trying to explain how improved warrior agro won't break the game to some of ours &quot;very intelligent&quot; visitors. From their perspective, quite a few are correct. After all, considering we have about 1500hp more than knights, higher AC (because as we all know, AC exceeding the soft cap is tremendously important), deal about 20-30% more damage than knights, and have far better mitigation due to our separate tables, and the super godly /disc defensive that apparently allows us to survive being hit full-force by a battering ram while knights get killed by the wind alteration tha ram's forward progression causes. Indeed, considering all of our massive advantages listed in the last sentence, giving us improved agro will surely break Everquest, especially considering knight spells are utterly useless.<br>
